<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-31T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-31T04:00:00-05:00" n="621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/3–3149: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Clark</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-31T17:00:00+08:00">March 31,
                                    1949—5 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received March 31—8:05 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Cantel 180. Notes on unencumbered balance special account exchanged.<note n="96" xml:id="d621fn96">For texts, see Department of State,
                                Treaties and Other International Acts Series No. 1923; or 63 Stat,
                                (pt. 3) 2425.</note> Documents being pouched.<note n="97" xml:id="d621fn97">Despatch No. 2, April 1, not printed.</note> [Re]
                            Department’s telCan 71, March 29.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department Cantel 180, repeated Nanking 166, Shanghai 121 for ECA
                            Griffin.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>